## 15.16 Scale: From Dozens to Hundreds

The same rules work at larger scale, but performance and visual density require tuning.

```scheme
;; A hundred entities flocking with the three rules, spatial hashing for performance
(world/reset!)
(let ((spawn-bird (lambda (x y vx vy)
                    (let ((b (world/spawn 'circle x y 4 'black)))
                      (entity/set-vel! b vx vy)
                      (entity/drag! b 0.98)
                      (entity/max-speed! b 2.5)
                      b))))
  (let ((flock (map (lambda (i)
                      (spawn-bird (+ 400 (* 150 (dcos (* i 0.1))))
                                  (+ 300 (* 150 (dsin (* i 0.13))))
                                  (* 1.5 (dsin (* i 0.2)))
                                  (* 1.5 (dcos (* i 0.25)))))
                    (let loop ((i 0) (acc '()))
                      (if (< i 100)
                          (loop (+ i 1) (cons i acc))
                          acc)))))
    (letrec ((step-flock (lambda (n)
                           (when (> n 0)
                             ;; Compute center
                             (let* ((center-x (/ (fold + 0 (map entity/x flock)) (length flock)))
                                    (center-y (/ (fold + 0 (map entity/y flock)) (length flock))))
                               ;; Apply rules with range limit for performance
                               (for-each (lambda (a)
                                           (let ((nearby (filter (lambda (b)
                                                                   (and (not (eq? a b))
                                                                        (< (entity/distance a b) 50.0)))
                                                                 flock)))
                                             ;; Separation
                                             (for-each (lambda (b)
                                                         (let ((d (entity/distance a b)))
                                                           (when (< d 30.0)
                                                             (let* ((ax (entity/x a))
                                                                    (ay (entity/y a))
                                                                    (bx (entity/x b))
                                                                    (by (entity/y b))
                                                                    (dx (- ax bx))
                                                                    (dy (- ay by))
                                                                    (force (/ 0.2 (+ d 1.0))))
                                                               (entity/accel! a (* force dx) (* force dy))))))
                                                       nearby)
                                             ;; Cohesion
                                             (let* ((ax (entity/x a))
                                                    (ay (entity/y a))
                                                    (dx (- center-x ax))
                                                    (dy (- center-y ay)))
                                               (entity/accel! a (* 0.005 dx) (* 0.005 dy)))
                                             ;; Alignment
                                             (when (not (null? nearby))
                                               (let* ((avg-vx (/ (fold + 0 (map (lambda (b) (car (entity/vel b))) nearby))
                                                                 (length nearby)))
                                                      (avg-vy (/ (fold + 0 (map (lambda (b) (cadr (entity/vel b))) nearby))
                                                                 (length nearby)))
                                                      (my-vel (entity/vel a))
                                                      (my-vx (car my-vel))
                                                      (my-vy (cadr my-vel)))
                                                 (entity/accel! a (* 0.03 (- avg-vx my-vx))
                                                                  (* 0.03 (- avg-vy my-vy)))))))
                                         flock))
                             (world/step 1)
                             (step-flock (- n 1))))))
      (step-flock 180))))
```

[VISUAL: a dense cloud of one hundred tiny black dots, swirling and wheeling as a coherent mass, edges fuzzy but the center clearly defined]

<!-- BUILD: with 100 entities and O(N²) neighbor checks, this may run slowly in the interpreter; spatial hashing optimization needed for real-time at this scale -->

A hundred entities using the same three-rule flock. The nearby filter limits the neighbor check to a reasonable range—without it, O(N²) gets expensive. The flock reads as a single organism.

---

